  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Jamaica safe for digital nomads?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Jamaica has higher crime than other Caribbean DNV destinations, but most nomads stay safe by choosing good areas (Montego Bay tourist areas, Ocho Rios, Negril, gated communities) and using common sense. Avoid walking alone at night, use registered taxis, and keep valuables secure.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Where should I live in Jamaica?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Popular nomad bases: Montego Bay (beaches, infrastructure), Ocho Rios (central, waterfalls), Negril (laid-back beach town), Kingston (urban, culture, but less safe). Treasure Beach offers quiet south coast vibes. Start in tourist areas.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How's the internet?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Variable. Urban areas and tourist towns have decent internet (25-100 Mbps possible). Rural areas are spotty. Always verify internet before committing to accommodation. Coworking spaces in Montego Bay offer reliable connectivity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I extend to 2 years?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, the DNV can be renewed for a second year. Apply before your first year expires with updated documentation. Same $100 fee and requirements apply.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about hurricanes?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Jamaica is in the hurricane belt. Season runs June-November, with September being peak risk. Have evacuation plans, understand your insurance coverage, and consider timing. Many nomads avoid August-October.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is $50,000/year enough for Jamaica?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes—Jamaica is affordable. At $50,000/year (~$4,100/month), you can live quite comfortably. Budget $1,500-2,500/month for expenses and save the rest. This is the main advantage of Jamaica over pricier Caribbean destinations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

